<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The new PoF</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I did not write this.  I just saw it posted on my old server boards and thought you may find it interesting.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Hello Gang...<br>
I just came from a fear raid where i was there from start to finish. The raid was able to take out everything but CT. We called in some extra people, and made an attemt at him but only got him to 50 before we were dead. I didnt get to see that actual battle, because i was the lowest level enchanter in the zone. I volunteered to Dispelle / tash.<br>
<br>
Here are some of my observations :<br>
<br>
<br>
1) We do a west wall break, and this was no more difficult than it normally is.<br>
<br>
2) We had 4 enchanters there ( 2 after shissar ). Enchanter levels were 60, 60, 55 (me) and 54. From my observation, mez worked similar to what you would expect for your level there. From casual observation, things were no more resistant than normal.<br>
<br>
3) Loot drops seemed to be upped. Every 3rd to 4th mob seemed to drop armor for the appropriate class, and while one run doesnt make a statistical sample, i had just been to hate a couple days before the patch and drops were abnormally high there as well. I believe the loot table drops were enhanced some.<br>
<br>
4) Dracolich was much different. He felt like a SoV mob kind of, and was MUCH more difficult than the old CT even. He was hitting for 600s ( according to our tanks ), and was a fairly long fight. I cant remember at this time if he DT ed or not. In our raid he dropped 2 Crimson robe of Adelines. (EDIT : Pimm and Selran got these)<br>
<br>
5) Fright (1st Demigod we faced) Deathtouches now, about as frequently as the old CT did. Still relatively easy, because it didnt seem like his HP was upped at all. Only casualties from this fight were the people he DTed ( the puller , and 1 other person i belive ). Fright dropped an amulate of necropolence ( the one that is 13 int -100 hp effect skeleton ). He had CT drop table, but only one item instead of four. He hit for 500s from what i was told by my tanks. (EDIT.. Mascen got amulate)<br>
<br>
6) Dread was similar to fright, in that he DT, Hit for 500s and had the same hit points as before. He dropped soul leech. (EDIT.. Icher got soul leech for SK epic)<br>
<br>
7) Terror was different... No DT, hit for 450s and had a WIDE range AoE cold based damage spell (spell message was something like &quot; you are blasted by freezing winds or some such &quot;). He also had a wide range dispell that the other 2 demigods didnt have, and he came with 2 amy knights. This fight was fairly difficult for us, because he kept dispelling the mezzes on the 2 amys that came with him. In the end he fell and dropped some item for necro Epic quest (slime blood ?), and .. um i cant remember what the second item was from him but it wasnt something worth remembering.<br>
(EDIT .. Nekrotic got slime blood)<br>
<br>
 (EDIT ... Removed a paragraph complaining about the lack of the enchanter epic mob spawning at all)<br>
<br>
9) info on the new CT from what i was told ( i tashed and dispelled so was gone in the beginning of the fight )<br>
<br>
: Hits for 600<br>
: Targetted dispell<br>
: massive knockback damage spell<br>
: tons of hit points<br>
: rampages often<br>
: No deathtouch that we noticed<br>
: did harmtouch someone in the beginning of the fight.<br>
<br>
I might be missing something but thats the gist of it. Raid only made one attempt cause everyone was tired.. and the first attempt was a more &quot; feeling out &quot; session anyway.<br>
<br>
On a side note, the iksar monk there was warmly to CT...<br>
<br>
Shaman epic iksar broodlings still spawn after the Demigods go down... Only thing missing was shissar.. /sigh /rude verant..<br>
<br>
Anyone else feel free to post your own observations on this thread, or your comments, or any questions. I will attempt to remember other details if prodded.<br>
<br>
Sharing all this info to help others out...<br>
<br>
